  "instructions": [
    "Rinse the Arab rice in cold water until it runs clear.",
    "In a large pot, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion and garlic; cook for about 2 minutes or until softened.",
    "Add Arab rice to the pot with half a cup of warm water. Stir well and add lemon juice and vinegar. Bring to a boil then reduce heat to low and cover the pot.",
    "Cook the mixture, stirring occasionally, until water is absorbed (about 10-15 minutes).",
    "Adjust seasoning with salt and black pepper as needed.",
